fy\_iceworld\_future Author: h4mx0r 200 years into the future, civilization has rediscovered a form of unparallelled entertainment to satisfy the human bloodlust. Gladitorial 'to the death' combat of a new era, displayed on pay-per-view television. In a remote oceanic location towards the extreme southern hemisphere, an arena was built specifically for the purpose of this televised event. Nano-Camera Drones fly around, invisible to the naked eye, recording and sending all the graphic footage straight to the Spectators in real-time. Designs of this specific arena were built to mimick the infamous 'iceworld skirmish of 1999'. This gigantic hunk of ice and metal is kept afloat by anti-gravitational orbs that float around the structure. The inner section of the arena is a pure reconstruction of the 'iceworld' and the outer limits are surrounded by guard towers to offer a strategic vantage point. Below the floating island are freezing waters of no return. The Terrorist and Counter-Terrorist teams are in it for the money, with $300 awarded per kill and more for each round they win. With a supply of clones limited only by the show's demand, this arena is sure to be one bloody warzone. NOTE: There is a bomb that can be planted next to the snowman in case a round gets dragged long. There is a second C4 up in the tower behind the CTs in case the first one is lost to the waters. There is once again a buy zone in the bombsite itself. Surviving winners get to stock up for the next round! Also this thing isn't really meant to be played with 64 players (hell, who plays CS with 64 players short of zombie mods?) but the option is there with 64 spawns. Also special thanks to TopHATTwaffle for his Realworldtextures2 pack (used for glass) and vanblam for his sci-fi texture pack (really cool textures)

=======

This map's MAIN SELLING POINT:  NO AWP.  We're tired of AWPers on iceworld.

If you have an account and appreciate this map, please approve it!

Also, I would like to add, we DID NOT DECOMPILE fy_iceworld_cssource to make this map.  We took dimensional measurements and built it from scratch, using fy_iceworld_cssource as a reference.  That's explained below.

=======
CREDITS:
=======
Thanks to Valve Software for making Steam, Half-Life, Counter Strike, Half-Life 2, Counter Strike Source, and the Hammer Editor

Thanks to RD for the original fy_iceworld for CS, available at http://www.fpsbanana.com/?section=viewitem.maps.maps.main.1719

Thanks to Mr.Stealth for fy_iceworld_cssource, on which this map is based in CSS, available at http://www.fpsbanana.com/?section=viewitem.maps.maps.main.3694.

This map is based ENTIRELY on fy_iceworld_cssource, which would not have been possible if not for everything above.  Thanks everyone.  Great job.

Finally, thanks to the entire 301net Team for all your hard work.
=======
NOTES:
=======
Reworked version of a retracted release.  Based on fy_iceworld_cssource.  Removed AWP, added dual-elites, removed lamps, made middle dividers translucent, changed ground texture, changed water texture, changed ice texture, changed bombsite letter, changed lighting.
Basically, we worked from fy_iceworld_cssource and made the changes that we wanted and about which we've seen discussed on our host.

The screenshots are from a previous version.  Textures not viewed in normal game-play are, appropriately, removed.

This is a remake of the classic fy_iceworld map, with a large visual overhaul and minor layout changes: the removal of the rear walls and the narrowing of the side routes. Furthermore, this map supports 64 players (hectic as it might be) and spawns additional weapons to accommodate this large number of players.
